File: An isolation room for people screened who test positive for COVID-19 symptoms. AFP/Luca Sola JOHANNESBURG - The health department said 29 more people have died of COVID-19 in South Africa. This brings the total number to 52,111. The number of confirmed cases is also up, now 1 537,852. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Gauteng braces for third wave That's an increase of 1,051 cases. The recovery rate stands at 95 percent with over 9.5 million tests conducted so far. In terms of the vaccine rollout, the number still stands at 182,983. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 537 852 the total number of deaths is 52 111 the total number of recoveries is 1 463 089 and the total number of vaccines administered is 182 983. pic.twitter.com/lRfJ4okLvh